<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 22.3pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">***</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amount shown includes the restricted stock units that vested and were paid to Mr.&nbsp;Shippar in the amount of $85,338 following his retirement as CEO. The amount shown also includes outstanding performance shares in an amount of $501,271 which are generally forfeited upon termination of employment unless the termination occurs because of retirement, death, or disability.&nbsp;The amount shown attributable to Mr.&nbsp;Shippar&#146;s retirement was calculated in the manner described in footnote&nbsp;3 to the Estimated Potential Payments Upon Termination Due to Retirement, Disability, or Death table on page&nbsp;41. The grant-date fair value of these restricted stock units and performance shares is also included in the amount shown for Mr.&nbsp;Shippar in column (d)&nbsp;above.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 23.05pt;text-indent:-18.55pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(7)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (d)&nbsp;for Mr.&nbsp;Shippar were calculated assuming he remained in the employ of the Company throughout the applicable vesting periods. Under the terms of the LTIP, Mr.&nbsp;Shippar&#146;s stock awards will be prorated as a result of his retirement. The prorated amount of performance shares for which he is eligible due to his retirement is shown in the Outstanding Equity Awards at Fiscal Year-End table on page&nbsp;32. The prorated amounts of restricted stock units and performance shares attributed to his retirement are also shown in column (h)&nbsp;above and in the Estimated Potential Payments Upon Termination Due to Retirement, Disability, or Death table on page&nbsp;41.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 5.75pt;text-indent:-5.75pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">GRANTS OF PLAN-BASED AWARDS 2010</font></b><a name="GrantsOfPlanbasedAwards2010_030744"></a></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following Grants of Plan-Based Awards table shows the range of each Named Executive Officer&#146;s annual and long-term incentive award opportunities granted for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31, 2010. The narrative following the table describes the terms of each incentive award opportunity.</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 5.75pt;text-indent:-5.75pt;"><hr size="1" width="25%" noshade color="black" align="left"></div>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">AIP awards are made under the AIP. Performance shares and restricted stock units (RSUs) are awarded under the LTIP.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(2)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Actual awards earned are shown in column (f)&nbsp;of the Summary Compensation Table on page&nbsp;26.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(3)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (k)&nbsp;reflect the grant-date fair value determined in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles using the same assumptions used in the valuation of compensation expense disclosed in Note 16 to the Company&#146;s Consolidated Financial Statements contained in the Annual Report, but based on the probable outcome of any performance conditions and excluding the effect of estimated forfeitures. The amounts shown for performance shares and restricted stock units are the values of the awards for accounting purposes; the value a Named Executive Officer realizes from performance shares will depend on actual Common Stock performance relative to the 27-company peer group </font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">discussed above, on page&nbsp;20, and market price appreciation and dividend yield. The value a Named Executive Officer realizes from restricted stock units will depend on the market value of Common Stock at the time of vesting.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(4)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Effective May&nbsp;1, 2010, upon becoming the Company&#146;s Chief Executive Officer, Mr.&nbsp;Hodnik received an additional grant to increase his long-term incentive opportunities as shown and his annual target incentive opportunity increased from 45&nbsp;percent to 60 percent.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(5)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown for AIP were calculated as of the grant date assuming Mr.&nbsp;Shippar remained in the employ of the Company throughout the applicable performance year. Under the terms of the AIP, Mr.&nbsp;Shippar&#146;s award was prorated as a result of his retirement. The amounts shown for RSUs and performance shares were calculated assuming Mr.&nbsp;Shippar remained in the employ of the Company throughout the applicable restricted stock unit vesting period and performance share performance period. Under the terms of the LTIP, Mr.&nbsp;Shippar&#146;s restricted stock units and performance shares will be prorated as a result of his retirement.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 5.75pt;text-indent:-5.75pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">GRANTS OF PLAN-BASED AWARDS DISCUSSION</font></b><a name="GrantsOfPlanbasedAwardsDiscussion_031418"></a></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company&#146;s 2010 incentive awards for all Named Executive Officers consisted of one annual incentive opportunity&#151;the AIP, and two long-term incentive opportunities&#151;performance shares and restricted stock units. Each incentive award is discussed below.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Annual Incentive Plan. </font></i><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For all the Named Executive Officers, the following were the 2010 AIP performance goals, goal weighting, and goal measures.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Strategic Goals</font></p>    </td>
<td width="2%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.68%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">%</font></p>    </td>
<td width="43%" colspan="5" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:43.92%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Various: See below</font></p>    </td>
<td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.08%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For purposes of the AIP, net income goals exclude non-operating income or loss and CFOA goals exclude pension contributions. Strategic goals for 2010 were related to the Company&#146;s ability to launch a new wind business venture, implementation of specific moves to reshape our generation supply and customer mix to reduce base load capacity, carbon emissions and customer concentration, development of a fully integrated talent development strategy to thoughtfully develop future leaders, and demonstration of continuous improvement of our safety, environmental and customer service values. Each AIP goal&#146;s achievement was independently measured. The actual amount of the target award opportunity earned is based on the goal weighting percentage assigned to the AIP performance goals achieved. The amounts shown in column (d)&nbsp;of the Grants of Plan-Based Awards table on page&nbsp;28 reflect the minimum AIP award that would be payable&#151;ranging from 11.3&nbsp;percent to 22.5 percent of base salary&#151;if both NI and CFOA results are at threshold and if there is no progress on strategic goals. The amounts shown in column (e)&nbsp;reflect the AIP target-level awards that would be payable&#151;ranging from 30 percent to 60 percent of base salary&#151;if both NI and CFOA results are at target and all strategic goals are determined to have been achieved at the target level. The amount shown in column (f)&nbsp;reflects maximum AIP awards that would be payable&#151;ranging from 60 percent to 120 percent of base salary&#151;if both NI and CFOA results are at superior and all strategic goals are determined to have been achieved at the superior level.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The CEO, with input from senior management, assesses the progress made on achieving the strategic goals and makes a recommendation to the Compensation Committee as to the degree to which such goals have been achieved. The Compensation Committee then approves each AIP goal achievement level. Actual 2010 NI exceeded the threshold by 7.4&nbsp;percent, or $5.2 million; CFOA exceeded target by 5.8&nbsp;percent, or $14 million; and overall strategic goals exceeded threshold. The resulting total AIP payout for 2010 was calculated as follows:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">29<a name="PB_29_032717_8146"></a></font></p>

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='29',FILE='C:\JMS\105686\11-8040-1\task4558599\8040-1-ba-09.htm',USER='105686',CD='Mar 18 03:25 2011' -->

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">As a result, the amounts shown in column (f)&nbsp;of the Summary Compensation Table on page&nbsp;26<b>  </b>include AIP awards earned at 101.2 percent of target in 2010, which ranged from 20 percent to 55 percent of base salary for the Named Executive Officers, and which reflect prorated opportunities for Mr.&nbsp;Hodnik and Mr.&nbsp;Shippar.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Named Executive Officers may elect to receive their AIP award in cash, or to defer some or all of it in accordance with SERP II. Named Executive Officers who retire, die, or become disabled during the year remain eligible to receive a prorated AIP award if the applicable performance goals are achieved. Named Executive Officers who terminate employment for any other reason forfeit the AIP award.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Performance Shares</font></i><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">. Three performance share awards, each encompassing a different three-year performance period, are reflected in the Summary Compensation Table on page&nbsp;26 for the year in which the performance period commenced. The performance share awards for the performance period beginning in 2010 are also reflected in the Grants of Plan-Based Awards table on page&nbsp;28. In 2010, the Named Executive Officers were granted performance share awards for the three-year performance period beginning on January&nbsp;1, 2010, and ending on December&nbsp;31, 2012. The number of shares of Common Stock that each Named Executive Officer will earn pursuant to the 2010 performance share awards will be based on the Company&#146;s TSR ranking relative to a 27-company peer group. A more detailed discussion of the TSR peer group is provided on page&nbsp;20.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (g)&nbsp;of the Grants of Plan-Based Awards table on page&nbsp;28 reflect the minimum 2010 performance share award payable, set at 50 percent of the target amounts shown in column (h), which will be earned if ALLETE&#146;s TSR for the three-year performance period ranks nineteenth among the peer group. The amounts shown in column (h)&nbsp;reflect the target performance share award payable if ALLETE&#146;s TSR for the three-year performance period ranks fourteenth among the peer group. The amounts shown in column (i)&nbsp;reflect the maximum performance share award payable, set at 200 percent of the target amount, which will be earned if ALLETE&#146;s TSR for the three-year performance period ranks fourth or higher among the peer group. A performance share award is earned at each ranking from nineteenth to first. Performance share awards earned at TSR rankings that fall between nineteenth, fourteenth and fourth are interpolated on a straight-line basis.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Dividend equivalents accrue during the performance period and are paid in shares, but only to the extent performance goals are achieved. If earned, 100 percent of the performance shares will be paid in Common Stock after the end of the performance period. A Named Executive Officer who retires, dies, or becomes disabled during the performance period remains eligible to receive a payment of performance shares if the applicable performance goals are achieved. The actual number of performance shares will be prorated to reflect the portion of the performance period actually worked. Upon a change in control, performance share awards would immediately pay out on a prorated basis, including dividend equivalents, at the greater of the target level or the level earned based on then-current actual TSR ranking as compared to the peer group companies. The grant-date fair value based on the probable outcome for performance shares awarded to each Named Executive Officer is included in the amounts shown in column (d)&nbsp;of the Summary Compensation Table on page&nbsp;26.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Performance shares awarded for both the 2010&#151;2012 and the 2009&#151;2011 performance periods remain unearned unless and until the performance goals are achieved at the end of the respective performance periods. The number of performance shares awarded to each Named Executive Officer for each of those periods is shown in column (h)&nbsp;of the Outstanding Equity Awards at Fiscal Year-End table on page&nbsp;32. An estimated market value of the unearned and unvested performance shares, assuming superior performance in the case of the 2010&#151;2012 performance period and target performance in the case of the 2009&#151;2011 performance period is shown in column (i)&nbsp;of that table. The actual value, if any, to the Named Executive Officers will be determined at the end of 2011 and 2012, respectively, based on the Company&#146;s actual TSR ranking for the three-year performance period relative to the peer group.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">During the three-year performance period 2008&#151;2010, the Company&#146;s shareholders realized a TSR of 8.3&nbsp;percent on their investment in Common Stock, ranking the Company ninth among the peer group of 16&nbsp;comparable companies for that performance period. As a result, the Named Executive Officers earned a target performance share payout for the 2008&#151;2010 performance period.</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">30<a name="PB_30_032736_7091"></a></font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">Restricted Stock Units</font></i><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">. The number of restricted stock units awarded to the Named Executive Officers in 2010 is shown in column (j)&nbsp;of the Grants of Plan-Based Awards table on page&nbsp;28. Each restricted stock unit entitles the Named Executive Officer to receive one share of Common Stock when the unit vests after the period of time specified in the award. The restricted stock units granted in 2010 vest on December&nbsp;31, 2012. The Named Executive Officers must remain employed by the Company at the time restricted stock units vest to receive the Common Stock. Dividend equivalents accrue during the vesting period and are paid in shares, but only to the extent that the restricted stock units actually vest. Upon the Named Executive Officer&#146;s retirement, disability, or death, or upon a change in control of the Company, a prorated number of the restricted stock units would vest immediately. The full grant-date fair value for restricted stock units awarded to each Named Executive Officer is included in the amount shown in column (d)&nbsp;of the Summary Compensation Table on page&nbsp;26. The number of unvested restricted stock units outstanding at the end of 2010, including dividend equivalents, is shown in column (f)&nbsp;of the Outstanding Equity Awards at Fiscal Year-End table on page&nbsp;32, while the value of the award as of December&nbsp;31, 2010, is shown in column (g).</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Subject to the relevant plan documents, the Compensation Committee has full discretion to determine the terms and conditions of awards under the AIP and LTIP programs. This discretion includes the ability to reduce or eliminate awards (and as to the AIP, to increase awards) regardless of whether applicable performance goals have been achieved. Outstanding LTIP awards, however, may not be adversely affected without the consent of the Named Executive Officer. The Compensation Committee did not exercise discretion to increase, reduce or eliminate awards during 2010.</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each option award has a ten-year term. Therefore, the grant date for each award is the date ten years prior to the date shown in column (e)&nbsp;except as to Mr.&nbsp;Shippar&#146;s awards. Options vest in three equal installments on each of the first, second, and third anniversaries of the grant date. Mr.&nbsp;Shippar retired on April&nbsp;30, 2010. His options then unexercisable became fully vested as of his retirement date. He has until the earlier of the original expiration date or three years from his retirement date to exercise all of his outstanding options.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(2)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (f)&nbsp;are comprised of the following: (1)&nbsp;the performance shares earned for the 2008&#151;2010 performance period, which amount for Mr.&nbsp;Shippar was prorated to reflect the 28/36</font><font size="1" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">th</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#160;months of the performance period during which he was employed by the Company, and which all Named Executive Officers received in Common Stock on February&nbsp;3, 2011; and (2)&nbsp;restricted stock units granted on February&nbsp;2, 2009, and January&nbsp;18, 2010, to each Named Executive Officer and additional grants to Mr.&nbsp;Hodnik on May&nbsp;12, 2009, and May&nbsp;1, 2010, plus dividend equivalents. Restricted stock units vest three years after the grant date provided the Named Executive Officer continues to be employed </font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">32<a name="PB_32_040552_4141"></a></font></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">by the Company. The restricted stock units granted to Mr.&nbsp;Shippar on February&nbsp;2, 2009, and January&nbsp;18, 2010, are shown in column (d)&nbsp;of the Option Exercises and Stock Vested table below because the restricted stock units vested on a prorated basis due to his retirement on April&nbsp;30, 2010.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 5.75pt;text-indent:-5.75pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(3)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (g)&nbsp;were calculated by multiplying the number of shares and units in column (f)&nbsp;by $37.26, the closing price of Common Stock on December&nbsp;31, 2010.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(4)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (h)&nbsp;represent the Common Stock that would be payable for outstanding performance share awards if target performance were achieved (a TSR ranking of fourteenth among the 27-company peer group) for the performance period 2009&#151;2011 and if superior performance was achieved (a TSR ranking of fourth among the 27-company peer group) for the performance period 2010&#151;2012. If the performance period would have ended on December&nbsp;31, 2010, performance shares would be earned at 70 percent of target for the 2009&#151;2011 performance period and 140 percent of target for the 2010&#151;2012 performance period. The amounts shown for Mr.&nbsp;Shippar reflect the prorated amounts for which he is eligible due to his April&nbsp;30, 2010, retirement.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 5.75pt;text-indent:-5.75pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(5)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (i)&nbsp;were calculated by multiplying the number of shares and units in column (h)&nbsp;by $37.26, the closing price of Common Stock on December&nbsp;31, 2010.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 5.75pt;text-indent:-5.75pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts in column (c)&nbsp;for SERP II reflect actual years of service with the Company. Credited service under Retirement Plan A (as defined below) stopped on September&nbsp;30, 2006, and under SERP I stopped on December&nbsp;31, 2004. Mr.&nbsp;Shippar and Mr.&nbsp;Hodnik&#146;s credited service under Retirement Plan B (as defined below) reflects the actual time that they were active participants in Retirement Plan B.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(2)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For the Named Executive Officers, except Mr.&nbsp;Shippar, the amounts shown in column (d)&nbsp;represent the discounted net present values of the annual annuity payments to which the Named Executive Officers would be entitled at retirement assuming they retire at age 62, the earliest age at which Named Executive Officers may receive unreduced pension benefits. Mr.&nbsp;Shippar retired on April&nbsp;30, 2010. The amounts shown for him represent the discounted net present value of the annuity payments he began receiving upon retirement. In addition to retirement age, the following assumptions were used to calculate the present value of accumulated benefits: discount rate of 5.36 percent; cost of living adjustment of 2.5&nbsp;percent; and female spouses are assumed to be three years younger than male spouses, except for Mr.&nbsp;Shippar for whom the calculation took into account his and his spouse&#146;s actual ages. The amounts reflect the accumulated pension benefits over the years of credited service shown for each plan.</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">34<a name="PB_34_041308_7906"></a></font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='34',FILE='C:\JMS\105686\11-8040-1\task4558599\8040-1-ba-11.htm',USER='105686',CD='Mar 18 03:35 2011' -->

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">PENSION BENEFITS DISCUSSION</font></b><a name="PensionBenefitsDiscussion_041311"></a></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Minnesota Power and Affiliated Companies Retirement Plan A (Retirement Plan A) is a tax-qualified defined benefit pension plan that covers the majority of our nonunion employees, including the Named Executive Officers. Pension benefits are based on the employee&#146;s years of service and the employee&#146;s final average earnings. Final average earnings covered by Retirement Plan A include the highest consecutive 48 months of salary and Results Sharing awards in the last 15 years of service. Results Sharing was a broad-based profit-sharing program that was available to virtually all of our employees prior to January&nbsp;2009. As the result of a Company-wide nonunion benefit change, Named Executive Officers have not accrued additional credited service under Retirement Plan A since September&nbsp;30, 2006. The pension benefit is calculated as a life annuity using the following formula:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div align="center">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100.0%;">
<tr>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.56%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="7%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:7.78%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">[</font></p>    </td>
<td width="7%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:7.78%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">0.8%</font></p>    </td>
<td width="6%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:6.66%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#215;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="35%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:35.96%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">years of credited service from July&nbsp;1, 1980 <br>   through September&nbsp;30, 2006</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.68%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">]</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.58%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#215;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="25%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:25.0%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">final   average earnings</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
</div>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">plus </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(for Named Executive Officers hired before July&nbsp;1, 1980)</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100.0%;">
<tr>
<td width="7%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:7.78%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="7%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:7.06%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">[</font></p>    </td>
<td width="7%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:7.06%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">10%</font></p>    </td>
<td width="4%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:4.44%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">+</font></p>    </td>
<td width="37%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:37.24%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1% &#215; years of credited service <br>   prior to July&nbsp;1, 1980)</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.84%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">]</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.58%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#215;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="25%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:25.0%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">final   average earnings</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Mr.&nbsp;Shippar and Mr.&nbsp;Hodnik are also entitled to a pension benefit under the Minnesota Power and Affiliated Companies Retirement Plan B (Retirement Plan B) based on positions each held previously. Retirement Plan B is a tax-qualified defined benefit pension plan that covers the majority of our union employees. The Retirement Plan B pension benefit is calculated as a life annuity using the following formula:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100.0%;">
<tr>
<td width="10%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:10.0%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="8%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:8.38%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">[</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.6%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">10%</font></p>    </td>
<td width="4%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:4.16%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">+</font></p>    </td>
<td width="30%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:30.5%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1% &#215; years of credited service)</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.3%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">]</font></p>    </td>
<td width="6%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:6.54%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#215;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="29%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:29.54%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">final   average earnings</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The 10 percent portion of the formulas is prorated, based on years of service, between Retirement Plan A and Retirement Plan B for Mr.&nbsp;Shippar. Final average earnings covered by Retirement Plan B include the highest consecutive 48 months of salary and Results Sharing awards in the last 10 years of service. The remaining terms of Retirement Plan B are substantially the same as Retirement Plan A (Retirement Plan A and Retirement Plan B are collectively referred to as the Retirement Plans).</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Normal retirement age under the Retirement Plans is age 65 with at least five years of continuous service with the Company. Named Executive Officers become eligible for an unreduced early retirement benefit at age 62 if they have at least 10 years of continuous service, or at age 58 if they have at least 40 years of continuous service. Named Executive Officers are first eligible for a reduced early-retirement benefit at age 50 with at least 10 years of continuous service. Early retirement benefits are calculated by reducing the retirement benefit by 4&nbsp;percent for each year and partial year between age 62 and the early retirement benefit commencement age. Mr.&nbsp;Hodnik and Mr.&nbsp;Schober are currently eligible to receive early retirement benefits. Ms.&nbsp;Amberg, Mr.&nbsp;McMillan and Mr.&nbsp;Adams have a vested Retirement Plan A benefit, but are not currently eligible to receive early retirement benefits. Mr.&nbsp;Shippar retired on April&nbsp;30, 2010, elected the normal form of benefit, and began receiving his Retirement Plan benefit on May&nbsp;31, 2010.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each Named Executive Officer is married. The normal form of Retirement Plan A benefit payment for married participants is a life annuity with a 60 percent surviving spouse benefit. The normal form of Retirement Plan B benefit payment for married participants is a life annuity with a 50 percent surviving spouse benefit. At normal retirement age, each optional form of benefit payment is the actuarial equivalent of the normal form of benefit payment for both Retirement Plans. The Retirement Plans do not provide for lump sum distributions unless the lump sum equivalent value is $10,000 or less. Once pension benefit payments have commenced, the benefit adjusts in future years to reflect changes in cost of living, with a maximum adjustment of 3 percent per year.</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">35<a name="PB_35_042618_3736"></a></font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Both the annual earnings that may be considered in calculating benefits under the Retirement Plans and the annual benefit amount that the Retirement Plans may deliver to a Named Executive Officer are limited by the Tax Code. The SERP Plans are designed to provide supplemental pension benefits, paid out of general Company assets, to eligible executives including the Named Executive Officers, in amounts sufficient to maintain total pension benefits upon retirement at the level which would have been provided by our Retirement Plans if benefits were not restricted by the Tax Code. The SERP formula is calculated as follows:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div align="center">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100.0%;">
<tr>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.56%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="7%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:7.78%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">[</font></p>    </td>
<td width="7%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:7.78%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">0.8%</font></p>    </td>
<td width="6%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:6.66%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#215;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="35%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:35.96%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">years of credited service from July&nbsp;1, 1980<br>   through retirement or termination date</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.68%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">]</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.58%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#215;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="25%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:25.0%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">SERP   final average earnings</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
</div>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">plus </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(for Named Executive Officers hired before July&nbsp;1, 1980)</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100.0%;">
<tr>
<td width="12%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:12.26%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.66%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">[</font></p>    </td>
<td width="6%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:6.84%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">10%</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.5%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">+</font></p>    </td>
<td width="33%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:33.32%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1% &#215; years of credited service <br>   prior to July&nbsp;1, 1980)</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.84%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">]</font></p>    </td>
<td width="5%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.58%;">
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#215;</font></p>    </td>
<td width="25%" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:25.0%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">SERP   final average earnings</font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The compensation generally used to calculate SERP benefits is the sum of a participant&#146;s (i)&nbsp;annual salary and Results Sharing awards in excess of the Tax Code limits imposed on Retirement Plan A and (ii)&nbsp;AIP awards. The earnings used for purposes of calculating SERP benefits are equal to the highest consecutive 48 months of such SERP compensation. The highest-consecutive 48-month compensation for (i)&nbsp;and (ii)&nbsp;above can result in different periods; however, both must fall within the last 15 years of service. The present value on December&nbsp;31, 2010, of each Named Executive Officer&#146;s SERP pension benefit is shown in the Pension Benefits table on page&nbsp;34. The 2010 increase in the SERP II pension benefit value for each Named Executive Officer is included in column (g)&nbsp;of the Summary Compensation Table on page&nbsp;26.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each Named Executive Officer has elected a date when SERP benefit payments will commence and has elected the form of benefit payment. The normal form of payment for SERP I benefits is a 15-year annuity. The optional form of payment for the SERP I benefits is a life annuity, which is the actuarial equivalent of the normal form of payment. The normal form of payment for SERP II is a 15-year annuity. The optional forms of payment for SERP&nbsp;II benefits are a life annuity or a lump sum, each of which is actuarially equivalent to the normal form of payment.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">SERP I benefits vest and become payable only if the Named Executive Officer retires after reaching age 50 with 10 years of service. SERP I payments commence upon retirement.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">SERP II benefits vest and become payable only if the Named Executive Officer (i)&nbsp;retires after reaching age 50 with 10 years service, (ii)&nbsp;becomes disabled after reaching age 50 with 10 years of service, or (iii)&nbsp;reaches age 50 after becoming disabled with 10 years of service. Vested SERP II benefit payments commence upon the earlier of retirement or disability, or if a disability occurs prior to vesting, the earlier of attaining age 65 or the date of death. The SERP II benefits accrued after December&nbsp;31, 2004, are accelerated upon a termination in connection with a change in control under the Severance Plan.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In all other respects, the eligibility requirements for SERP retirement benefits and the calculation of SERP early retirement benefits mirror Retirement Plan A&#146;s eligibility requirements and early retirement benefits discussed above.</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">36<a name="PB_36_043133_9621"></a></font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 5.75pt;text-indent:-5.75pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 5.75pt;text-indent:-5.75pt;"><hr size="1" width="25%" noshade color="black" align="left"></div>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (c)&nbsp;include the following amounts: (i)&nbsp;salary earned and deferred in 2010 that was also reported in column (c)&nbsp;of the Summary Compensation Table on page&nbsp;26: Mr.&nbsp;Schober&#151;$55,615 and Mr.&nbsp;McMillan&#151;$24,212; and (ii)&nbsp;compensation that was earned and deferred in 2010 that was also reported in column (f)&nbsp;of the 2010 Summary Compensation Table: Mr.&nbsp;Schober&#151;$128,878, Ms.&nbsp;Amberg&#151;$53,636 and Mr.&nbsp;McMillan&#151; $39,693.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(2)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (d)&nbsp;reflect compensation that was earned and deferred in 2010 that was also reported in column (h)&nbsp;of the Summary Compensation Table.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(3)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (e)&nbsp;represent unrealized and realized earnings, including above-market interest earned in 2010 on nonqualified deferred balances, which was also reported in column (g)&nbsp;of the Summary Compensation Table as follows: Mr.&nbsp;Shippar&#151;$1,805 and Mr.&nbsp;Schober&#151;$1,043. Above-market interest was calculated using a 5.32 percent rate of return, which exceeds 120 percent of the applicable federal long-term rate of 4.24 percent.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .2in;text-indent:-.2in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(4)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The amounts shown in column (g)&nbsp;for the aggregate balance for the SERP II includes compensation that was previously earned and reported in 2008 and 2009 on the Summary Compensation Table as follows: Mr.&nbsp;Hodnik&#151;$5,153, Mr.&nbsp;Schober&#151;$318,522, Ms.&nbsp;Amberg&#151;$128,743, Mr.&nbsp;McMillan&#151;$151,984, Mr.&nbsp;Adams&#151;$21,603, and Mr.&nbsp;Shippar&#151;$415,506. These amounts have since been adjusted for investment performance (i.e., earnings and losses) and deferrals credited during 2010. The aggregate balances shown for the SERP I and the Minnesota Power and Affiliated Companies Executive Investment Plan II include compensation that was previously earned and reported in the Summary Compensation Table prior to 2008 and have since been adjusted for investment performance (i.e., earnings and losses).</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">37<a name="PB_37_044121_563"></a></font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='37',FILE='C:\JMS\105686\11-8040-1\task4558599\8040-1-ba-13.htm',USER='105686',CD='Mar 18 03:40 2011' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The SERP also provides a supplemental defined contribution benefit and a deferral account benefit. The SERP supplemental defined contribution benefit is designed to provide Named Executive Officers a benefit that is substantially equal to the benefit they would have been entitled to receive if the Tax Code did not impose limitations on the types and amounts of compensation that can be included in the benefit calculations under the Flexible Compensation Plan and RSOP. Annually, each Named Executive Officer may elect to defer to a SERP II deferral account, on a before-tax basis, some or all of his or her salary and AIP award. Named Executive Officers whose base salary is below the tax-qualified benefit plan&#146;s annual compensation limits may also elect to defer some or all of the SERP II defined contribution benefit. Named Executive Officers can select among different crediting rates to apply to deferral balances under the SERP Plans, which primarily match the investment options available to all employees under the RSOP. These investment options include mutual funds and similar investments. The Named Executive Officers may change their investment elections at any time. The amount of the 2010 SERP II defined contribution benefit received by each Named Executive Officer is included in column (h)&nbsp;of the Summary Compensation Table on page&nbsp;26. The aggregate amount each Named Executive Officer elected to defer and the amount that the Company contributed to the SERP II in 2010 is shown in the Nonqualified Deferred Compensation table on page&nbsp;37.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each Named Executive Officer has elected a date when benefit payments from his or her SERP I and SERP II deferral accounts will commence and has elected the form of benefit payment. Generally, SERP I and SERP II deferral account benefit payments will not begin earlier than the elected commencement date. However, for contributions made prior to January&nbsp;1, 2005, the full SERP I deferral account balance will be paid prior to the scheduled commencement date to any Named Executive Officer who is not eligible to retire at the time he or she terminates employment with the Company. In addition, a Named Executive Officer may request an early distribution of some or all of his or her SERP I deferral account balance upon a demonstrated severe financial need, or at any time prior to the first scheduled payment date, may elect an early withdrawal of contributions made to his or her account prior to January&nbsp;1, 2005, subject to a 10 percent early withdrawal penalty.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A Named Executive Officer is not allowed to elect to receive an early withdrawal of amounts contributed after January&nbsp;1, 2005, to his or her SERP II deferral account, except that he or she may request early withdrawal in the event of an unforeseen emergency, which request is subject to the approval of the Compensation Committee. Contributions made to a SERP II deferral account after December&nbsp;31, 2004, will be paid in full upon a termination of employment in connection with a change in control.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A Named Executive Officer may elect to receive his or her SERP deferral account balance in the form of either a lump sum payment or monthly installments over a 5-, 10-, or 15-year period, or a combination of both. A Named Executive Officer who retires will receive a fixed 7.5 percent annual interest crediting rate on his or her deferral account balance until paid in full.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Prior to 1996, the Company also provided executives an opportunity to elect to defer salary and AIP awards under the Minnesota Power and Affiliated Companies Executive Investment Plan II (EIP II), a nonqualified deferred compensation plan. Deferrals pursuant to such opportunity ended in 2002 and EIP II has been closed to new contributions since then. The Company resets the crediting rate under the EIP II annually at 120 percent of the rolling average of the 10-year Treasury Note. The EIP II benefits become payable upon retirement in the form of monthly annuity payments over a 5-, 10-, or 15-year period as elected by the executive. Generally, EIP II benefit payments will not begin earlier than the elected commencement date. However, the Named Executive Officer may request an early distribution of some or all of his EIP II account balance upon a demonstrated severe financial need, or at any time prior to the first scheduled payment date, he or she may elect an early withdrawal of his account balance subject to a 10 percent early withdrawal penalty.</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">38<a name="PB_38_044222_9497"></a></font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='38',FILE='C:\JMS\105686\11-8040-1\task4558599\8040-1-ba-15.htm',USER='105686',CD='Mar 18 03:50 2011' -->

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">POTENTIAL PAYMENTS UPON TERMINATION OR CHANGE IN CONTROL</font></b><a name="PotentialPaymentsUponTerminationO_044226"></a></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Severance Plan covers each Named Executive Officer as well as other key executives (collectively, Participants). Under the Severance Plan, a change in control of ALLETE generally means any one of the following events:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Acquisition by any person, entity, or group acting together of more than 50 percent of the total fair market value or total voting power of the Company&#146;s Common Stock;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Acquisition in any 12-month period of 40 percent or more of the Company&#146;s assets by any person, entity, or group acting together;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Acquisition in any 12-month period of 30 percent or more of the total voting power of the Company&#146;s Common Stock by any person, entity, or group acting together; or</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A majority of members of the Board of Directors is replaced during any 12-month period.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each Named Executive Officer is entitled to receive specified benefits in the event his or her employment is involuntarily terminated six months before or up to two years after a change in control. An involuntary termination is deemed to occur if (i)&nbsp;the Company terminates the employment of the Named Executive Officer other than for cause, or (ii)&nbsp;the Named Executive Officer resigns from his or her employment with good reason. Cause generally includes reasons such as failure to perform duties, willful misconduct, or felony convictions. Good reason generally means a material reduction in the Named Executive Officer&#146;s responsibilities or authority; a material reduction in his or her supervisor&#146;s responsibilities or authority; a material reduction in base salary, incentive compensation, or other benefits; a material breach by the Company of an agreement under which a Named Executive Officer provides services; or reassignment to another geographic location more than 50 miles from the Named Executive Officer&#146;s current job location.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Under the Severance Plan, Mr.&nbsp;Hodnik, Mr.&nbsp;Schober and Ms.&nbsp;Amberg would be entitled to receive a lump sum severance payment of 2.5 times their annual compensation. Mr.&nbsp;Adams and Mr.&nbsp;McMillan would receive a severance payment of 1.5 times their annual compensation. Mr.&nbsp;Shippar&#146;s participation in the Severance Plan ended upon his retirement; therefore, he would not be entitled to receive any severance payment. Annual compensation includes base salary and an amount representing a target award under the AIP in effect for the year of termination. The Severance Plan also provides a lump sum benefit continuation payment to Mr.&nbsp;Hodnik, Mr.&nbsp;Schober, and Ms.&nbsp;Amberg approximately equal in value to the benefits (as specified below) that they would have received had they remained in the employ of the Company after their termination for an additional 2.5 years, and in the case of Mr.&nbsp;Adams and Mr.&nbsp;McMillan, an additional 1.5&nbsp;years. The lump sum benefit continuation payment includes the value of the following benefits: (i)&nbsp;premiums for medical, dental, and basic group term life insurance benefits; (ii)&nbsp;Company contributions under the Flexible Benefit Plan; and (iii)&nbsp;the present value of additional SERP II benefits the Participant would have received under the SERP II had employment continued for 2.5 or 1.5 years after the later of the change in control or termination, as applicable. As a condition of receiving payments under the Severance Plan, Participants must sign a waiver of potential claims against the Company, and must agree not to disclose confidential information, engage in any business in competition with the Company for a period of one year, recruit any employee or director of the Company for employment for a period of two years, or publicly criticize the Company.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Upon a change in control, awards under the AIP would be calculated as if the end of the performance year had occurred, based on the Company&#146;s performance through the date of the change in control. AIP awards could range from zero to 200 percent of the target award opportunity depending on actual goal results. The SERP II also provides for a lump sum payment of benefits earned after December&nbsp;31, 2004, through the termination of employment in connection with a change in control. Under the LTIP, if a change in control were to occur, unvested stock options would immediately vest, restricted stock units would immediately vest on a prorated basis, and performance share awards would immediately pay out on a prorated basis at the greater of target level or the level earned based on then-current actual TSR ranking as compared to the peer group companies.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The total amount of severance payments due under the Severance Plan plus any payments accelerated under the AIP, LTIP, and SERP II due to a change in control will be limited to an amount which would result in no portion of such amount being subject to excise tax under Section&nbsp;4999 of the Tax Code, unless the payment would have to </font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">39<a name="PB_39_044305_3641"></a></font></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='39',FILE='C:\JMS\105686\11-8040-1\task4558599\8040-1-ba-15.htm',USER='105686',CD='Mar 18 03:50 2011' -->

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;"><a href="#TableOfContents" title="Click to go to Table of Contents">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">be reduced to an amount less than 85 percent of the amount the Named Executive Officer would otherwise have received, absent the imposition of the excise tax. If payments to a Named Executive Officer would be reduced to an amount less than 85 percent of the amount the Named Executive Officer would otherwise have received, total payments would not be reduced and the Named Executive Officer would instead receive an additional gross-up payment that would provide the Named Executive Officer with the same net after-tax payment the Named Executive Officer would have received if the excise tax had not applied to any of the payments.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">As described previously in 2011 Executive Compensation Changes starting on page&nbsp;24, the following plan provisions relating to a change in control were amended in January&nbsp;2011:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Severance Plan was amended effective January&nbsp;19, 2011, to eliminate the excise tax gross-up feature, to eliminate benefit continuation payments, and to establish a modified severance payment cap whereby the severance payment would be reduced to a level below the safe harbor amount if the executive would receive a higher after tax benefit than if the executive were to pay the applicable excise tax on the full payment amount.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The AIP was amended effective January&nbsp;1, 2011, to provide that in the event of a Change in Control (as defined by the AIP), any award earned pursuant to the AIP will be prorated based on the number of months in the performance year which had elapsed as of the date of a Change in Control.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Estimated Potential Payments Upon Termination Associated With a Change in Control</font></b><a name="EstimatedPotentialPaymentsUponTer_044328"></a></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">If a change in control had occurred on December&nbsp;31, 2010, prior to the plan changes listed above, and if, as a result, a Named Executive Officer&#146;s employment was terminated on the same date, the following table illustrates the value that the Named Executive Officer would have received.</font></p>

<tr>
<td width="25%" valign="top" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;border:none;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:25.54%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 10.0pt;text-indent:-10.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Severance Payment(1)</font></p>    </td>
